content.description: Unknown problem to the right of Sunday Vibes on the 1st Boulder. Sit start on a good in-cut edges. Make moves up the face on good edges and pinches to a big move to a slopey lip. Topout up the slab.
content.location: Obvious face climb to the 10 or 15 feet right of Sunday Vibes on the 1st Boulder.

content.description: Stand start on jugs. Climb the hueco tube feature to good holds over the lip and mantle.
content.protection: Pads. Small landing in between rhodos.
content.location: On the back side of 1st boulder. Starts a couple feet left of low cave on obvious feature.

content.description: Start under the roof on double underclings and work your way out through some core tension-y moves.
content.location: Cross the road and follow the river down stream until you find the first climbable boulder. 10 minute walk or so from the parking lot.

content.description: Sit start on two right facing side pulls and work up some small holds to an easy mantle.
Start on slopey ramp side pull and move left to gain the arête. Traverse to the right to a hang and drop.
There could be beta to make it easier than v8, only sussed one method and didn't check for anything else.
content.location: Start on the straight up and down sidepull/bar on the far left of the boulder. Do some harder moves to gain the jugs on the face and topout the arete.

content.description: Stand start on two small pockets (about two fingers each) and work your way straight to the top on some iron bands.
Start on a good hold and make hard moves out the roof.
content.location: 40 minute walk upstream from Jett Bridge Access

content.description: Start with left hand gaston triangle and right hand on crimp to make a big right hand move. Make some tricky moves out right, then to a big left handed dyno. Or use some gnarly crimps through the face to bypass this. Top out with a slopey mantle to finish up this stellar line.
content.location: Up river about 25 minutes from Sunday Vibes

content.description: Start in on jug flake on pedestal. Climb out rail feature to jug at the lip. Turn the lip and establish on slab to finish (I couldn't quite go no hands, but there is a sloping knob on the slab to match as a finish hold).
content.protection: A couple pads to protect the rock and the crux.
content.location: West Jett. First roof past Bad Blood. Obvious line on the left end of the roof

content.description: Sit start low on two small sloper crimps with a jug foot. Work your way straight out the roof and finish up on Rock Lee. This problem requires opening at least 6 Inner Gates to send.

Start on blocky undercling jugs and do some moves out the roof to gain the flat edge on the face. Follow the holds left to gain some good jugs and topout straight up. The topout is not a gimme, it's probably v6 alone.
content.protection: 3 pads would work but 4-5 is better. The more the merrier.
content.location: The obvious line that climbs out of the roof over the sloped rock to the left of 1st Boulder/Sunday Vibes v10.

content.description: Start on slopey holds to make a big starting move. Continue up slopers to finish on a jug to hang and drop. Fairly tall but the top is too mossy to clean.

Sit/lay down start low under double stacked roof with good pinches and heel hook edge. Movie straight up on edges and block undercling to flat jug at the lip. The roots of the tree are on for the top out. Go no hands to complete.
content.protection: Maybe a pad or a couple sliders. Soft ground and dab potential.
content.location: On 1st Boulder, a couple yards past the main wall. The ground is very close to the wall here, but it goes down pretty deep in there. This problem is in the middle of the overhang directly below the obvious tree set ~18in from the lip of the boulder.
